Rating: 3
I used tiger shrimp (one step up from jumbo), upped the garlic, substituted vermouth for white wine and served over braised escarole. Instead of peppers I added crushed red pepper flakes at the same time I added the vermouth, turned up the heat and let the whole thing come to a lively simmer for another minute. The flavors came together in grand fashion. Great dish. If I could train myself to make a dish more than once I would definitely add this to the repetoire.

Rating: 4
Fabulous! Up the garlic a bit, use extra olive oil, and pour it over angel hair pasta when serving. Don't skip the salt-water soak for the shrimp- it really adds flavor. I sautee fresh spinach in a separate pan with olive oil, garlic, and salt. Arrange spinach over pasta, top with shrimp, drizzle with oil and garlic from pan. Butter would be nice too, but my health-freak husband won't allow it. Oh, well, still delish.

