Rating: 3
A great classic. I add the wine earlier for 2 reasons; it needs longer to cook off the alcohol and you risk overdoing the shrimp if you don't. The first time I made this the "30 seconds of cooking to evaporate alcohol" caused the dipping sauce to be too wine flavored (I used chardonnay). OK, I'll try it one more time with a lighter wine, say a sauvignon blanc.

Rating: 3
I made a few changes in the recipe because it sounded a little too bland for me. I mixed this recipe with the SEARED SHRIMP WITH WARM NEW POTATO SALAD. I did the marinate and then I sprikle Goya Abodo Seasoning all over the shrimp. Then in the skillet I sauteed 1/3 cup of chopped shallots and 2 Tbls of Rosemary . I also used extra garlic - 2 extra cloves in the skillet and added all the marinated juice. That combo is very flavorful!

