Rating: 4
Boost the garlic to 5 cloves. Make a garlic and oil spaghetti, 8 oz dry spaghetti is about enough for this recipe. A steamed green vegetable for contrast. Spaghetti onto plate, arrange shrimp on top of spaghetti, sprinkle parsley over shrimp/pasta, finish with a sqeeze of lemon for a final touch. Mixed green salad and bread. Nummy.

Rating: 3
I had guests come over on Good Friday and made this dish as an appetizer. It was a huge success. I took the advice of some of the others that rated this recipe and added one additional clove of garlic as well as lemon at the end.

Rating: 2
Rather than adding peppers, delete. Increase garlic to three cloves, add 2 tbs of butter. Broil rather than sautee and when served, spritz with a scant flavoring of lemon. This recipe is hearty, flavorful, and carries the richness of butter without being overwhelming.

